As a depiction of the times that these films were made in they serve a function of a biased time machine. One gets an idea of the kind of life people may have aspired to lead. An idea of the fashions, the trends, the values of the era. For the generations that did not live in the era of the filming os such movies they are somewhat intriguing. Beyond the novelty of the film's content, I remain unimpressed by the story and characters who defy any semblance to any beings that could potentially be encountered corporeal or otherwise. It was so fantastical and yet not enough at the same time I fear the wirter may have over and undershot at the same time. The direction was not bad, better than most other films in this genre as was the photography.
different than what I was looking for but very entertaining. I little over board with the cat scene but fun

As a paying customer and adult, I'm highly offended that I am not getting what I paid for to see!!!  I'm trying to collect rare and vintage films as they were made and can't for ever sex scene is taken out!!! This makes the movie jump all over the place!!!

FEMALE ANIMAL (1969)
She's all female and all animal, seduced by drugs, wealth and power. Angelique must choose between decadence and self-respect in 'Female Animal'. Guess which prevails? You guessed right, this little minx gets corrupted faster than a politician in D.C. in this lurid, libidinous European example of sexploitation that's equal parts erotic and eurotrash. Copious amount of nudity, late 60's sleaze and a sexually-charged leading actress make this one radiate on your retro-radar. Highly enjoyable excesses abound - a hayride for the horndogs. Easily the superior film in this two-fer filth-fest.

TEENAGE MOTHER (1965)
She's a motor-cycle momma! Drugs, hormones and a hot new teacher send local high-school rabble-rousers over the edge in 'Teenage Mother'. See the film that shocked parents across the country, and probably bored the pants off their kids... A campy cautionary tale that's more joke than anything else, but typical for that mid-60's time frame when censors gave one last shot at saving our young'ins from going to hell in a Harley-Davidson heartbeat.
A bad film made watchable by its high level of cheeky camp and melodramatic overacting.
